{
  "texts": [
    "StackOverflow foot_11 is also a common source of code data.",
    "As a Question-and-Answer (Q&A) community dedicated to programming and development, it features questions and answers spanning topics such as programming languages, development tools, and algorithms.",
    "StackOverflow is part of StackExchange foot_12, which houses different Q&A sections.",
    "Therefore, it is categorized as social media data, as explained in Section 2.1.7.",
    "More recently, phi-1 (Gunasekar et al, 2023) is created specifically for training code models."
  ]
}